2026-02-04 21:35:23,823 - app.indexing.ddl_utils - INFO - Generated DDL for jobuser_sumtotal: -- This table maps each person to their specific job details. It connects an individual to a predefined job template and stores details unique to that job role, such as their joining date and primary rol...
CREATE TABLE jobuser_sumtotal (
  jobtemplatefk BIGINT -- Job Template Foreign Key -- A foreign key that links this job to a predefined job template. The template contains the standard details of the role, such as its title and core functions.,
  personfk BIGINT -- Person Foreign Key -- The foreign key that identifies the employee by linking to their record in the Person table. It is the essential link that defines 'who' holds this job role.,
  isprimary BIGINT -- Is Primary -- A flag that indicates if this is the employee's primary job, especially when a person can hold more than one role.,
  joiningdate TIMESTAMP -- Joining Date -- The date when the employee officially started in this specific job role.,
  authlstary TEXT -- Authorization List Array -- A system field that stores a list of permissions or access groups associated with this job role.,
  notetext TEXT -- Note Text -- A free-text field for any additional notes or comments related to this job role.,
  synchfaultflg BIGINT -- Synchronization Fault Flag -- A system flag indicating if an error occurred while synchronizing this record with another system.,
  synchfaultcntlstary TEXT -- Synchronization Fault Count List Array -- A system field that stores details or counts related to data synchronization errors.,
  objtypcd BIGINT -- Object Type Code -- A system code used to classify the type of this record.,
  deleted BIGINT -- Deleted Flag -- A flag indicating that this job role is no longer active but is kept for historical records.,
  mvpbatchid BIGINT -- MVP Batch ID -- An identifier for the batch process that created or last updated this record.,
  createddate TIMESTAMP -- Created Date -- The exact date and time when this job role record was created.,
  jobname TEXT -- Job Name -- The descriptive name of the job role (e.g., 'Senior Analyst'). This is likely copied from the job template for convenient access.,
  jobnum TEXT -- Job Number -- The unique business code or number for the job role. This is likely copied from the job template for convenient access.
);
